FBIS4-30840 "dreeu105_i_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbs Violate Cease-Fire in Sarajevo Zone Serbs Violate Cease-Fire in Sarajevo Zone AU3105194294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 31 May 94 AU3105194294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Report by Jadranko Milosevic and Zvonko Maric] [Excerpt] While the military observers of the United Nations are trying to keep their promise given in the Sarajevo UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] headquarters that they will convince the chetnik forces not to fire (?133) mm guns and the M-46 and M-48, which are popularly known in the aggressor army as chetnik nightingales, from the village of (?Gaj) inside the 20 km exclusion zone, the chetniks from (?Hadzici) on the other side have been attacking at irregular time intervals the lines of the fighters of the Army of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina on the southern sector of the Hadzici front with 120mm and 80mm mortars all day today. As we have learned from the command of the 9th Hill Brigade, 19 mortar shells landed on the positions of our fighters this afternoon alone. They were fired from Zunovaca, which is also inside the 20 km exclusion zone. The village of Loste was not spared shelling either. It was hit by five shells. [passage omitted]
